WEBVTT

1
00:01:38.870 --> 00:01:41.270
Hey... What's that song?

2
00:01:43.070 --> 00:01:47.350
Cut! Cut!
Who let that creep in here?


3
00:01:48.670 --> 00:01:50.150
Spongers!

4
00:01:50.350 --> 00:01:53.950
Throw him the hell out of here!
What do we pay you for?


5
00:02:01.470 --> 00:02:04.950
SERGEI BODROV

6
00:02:06.350 --> 00:02:09.550
-Your name?
- Bagrov.


7
00:02:11.270 --> 00:02:13.150
Danila Sergeyevich.

8
00:02:13.350 --> 00:02:16.750
Born 1975.
Station Street, 22.


9
00:02:19.070 --> 00:02:23.750
- Place of work?
- Haven't finished being demobbed yet.


10
00:02:28.350 --> 00:02:31.950
-Where did you serve?
- In the army.


11
00:02:33.350 --> 00:02:37.750
-Want to work for us?
- No.


12
00:02:43.270 --> 00:02:47.150
You broke their security guy's arm.
And nearly took his eye out.


13
00:02:47.550 --> 00:02:50.470
If you'd been drunk,
I'd have arrested you.


14
00:02:51.470 --> 00:02:52.950
Get outta here!

15
00:02:54.870 --> 00:02:58.750
If you don't get a job within a week,
I'll put you on probation.


16
00:03:05.270 --> 00:03:08.950
VIKTOR SUKHORUKOV

17
00:03:28.870 --> 00:03:32.150
I really broke his arm?

18
00:03:33.670 --> 00:03:35.750
No. Just dislocated it.

19
00:03:41.470 --> 00:03:46.350
And that guy who was screaming?
Who is he?


20
00:03:47.670 --> 00:03:49.150
The director.

21
00:03:57.870 --> 00:04:03.350
-And what was that song?
- ''Wings'' by Nautilus.


22
00:04:09.670 --> 00:04:14.270
SVETLANA PISMICHENKO

23
00:04:16.870 --> 00:04:20.870
Sergei Bagrov,
born 1942,


24
00:04:21.070 --> 00:04:22.950
...repeat convictions for burglary.

25
00:04:23.950 --> 00:04:26.950
He was killed in a prison camp
in January '82.


26
00:04:29.870 --> 00:04:31.750
He was my classmate.

27
00:04:34.270 --> 00:04:38.070
YURI KUZNETSOV

28
00:04:39.670 --> 00:04:43.350
Do you have ''Wings'' by Nautilus?
The CD?


29
00:04:47.550 --> 00:04:51.470
Whadda you want? Get out of here,
or I'll call the police.


30
00:04:54.870 --> 00:04:57.950
VYACHESLAV BUTUSOV

31
00:05:04.870 --> 00:05:07.750
You could at least chop wood
ratherthan sticking your neck out.


32
00:05:08.270 --> 00:05:10.150
Would have been betterto stay
in the army.


33
00:05:10.350 --> 00:05:12.550
Here they'll probably kill you,
idiot.


34
00:05:12.870 --> 00:05:15.750
Always turning on that metal of yours.

35
00:05:18.070 --> 00:05:21.750
You'll croak in prison
like your good-for-nothing father.


36
00:05:25.870 --> 00:05:30.270
The only hope I have
is my little Viktor.


37
00:05:30.470 --> 00:05:35.150
He's a big man there, you know,
in Leningrad.


38
00:05:45.350 --> 00:05:50.750
Just look at these. So little.
How cute you all were.


39
00:05:50.950 --> 00:05:54.150
-Just look.
- I've seen them.


40
00:05:54.350 --> 00:05:55.950
Take another look.

41
00:05:57.270 --> 00:06:01.150
You had better go to your brother
in Leningrad.


42
00:06:02.870 --> 00:06:07.350
I'll die soon, you know,
and he's to you like father now.


43
00:06:07.670 --> 00:06:09.550
This is your blood.

44
00:06:09.870 --> 00:06:13.550
The closest person to you
in this world.


45
00:06:15.270 --> 00:06:17.150
My little Viktor.

46
00:06:21.870 --> 00:06:27.470
BROTHER

47
00:06:28.670 --> 00:06:31.950
If you haven't seen Moscow,
you haven't seen much.


48
00:06:36.270 --> 00:06:39.750
The Chechen was released.
We need to take him out.


49
00:06:40.550 --> 00:06:42.470
He grabbed the whole market.

50
00:06:42.670 --> 00:06:46.070
Says it was his.
He's collecting from our spots.


51
00:06:46.270 --> 00:06:49.750
At the meet we agreed all peaceful,
like our people don't want war.


52
00:06:49.950 --> 00:06:52.950
But he and Paramon are close...

53
00:06:54.150 --> 00:06:56.550
The Chechen's going down!

54
00:06:59.270 --> 00:07:01.150
In short, fifteen.

55
00:07:03.670 --> 00:07:06.750
You know me. My prices are fair.

56
00:07:08.270 --> 00:07:10.150
Fifteen...

57
00:07:10.550 --> 00:07:16.270
That's good money, of course,
but forthe Chechen...


58
00:07:18.150 --> 00:07:20.070
With him I'm risking my skull.

59
00:07:22.270 --> 00:07:26.070
- How much?
- Twenty. And ten up front.


60
00:07:41.470 --> 00:07:43.350
You get a week for prepwork.

61
00:07:45.950 --> 00:07:47.750
Two.

62
00:07:51.070 --> 00:07:52.950
The Tatar's becoming a wiseguy.

63
00:07:53.870 --> 00:07:55.750
He took a lot up front.

64
00:07:56.670 --> 00:08:00.550
You guys hang up at the market day
and night, and keep out of sight.


65
00:08:01.870 --> 00:08:06.150
Bite off more than you can chew
and you wind up in the zoo.


66
00:09:45.670 --> 00:09:49.550
- Do you have ''Wings'' by Nautilus?
- No. They go quickly.


67
00:09:49.870 --> 00:09:52.750
But you stop in again. We should get
another shipment.


68
00:09:53.670 --> 00:09:56.550
- Have you anything else?
- Of course.


69
00:09:58.270 --> 00:10:03.550
Here's ''Titanic on the Fontanka''
with Grebenschikov.


70
00:10:03.870 --> 00:10:06.550
And this is ''Ten-year Report''

71
00:10:07.350 --> 00:10:09.750
Their best songs covered by friends.

72
00:10:09.950 --> 00:10:11.750
How much they cost?

73
00:10:11.950 --> 00:10:14.950
This one's 75,800. 
The other one's

74
00:11:12.470 --> 00:11:14.750
Well, what we selling, wino?

75
00:11:17.350 --> 00:11:19.350
You got watches?

76
00:11:19.550 --> 00:11:21.750
Well, my cut's fifty now.

77
00:11:21.950 --> 00:11:24.950
From you, you fucking worm, I said!

78
00:11:25.670 --> 00:11:28.550
And what did you think?
Taxes.


79
00:11:28.870 --> 00:11:33.470
- But I haven't sold anything yet!
- I'm confiscating the goods.


80
00:11:33.870 --> 00:11:38.350
But, sonny, ljust...
I haven't sold anything yet.


81
00:11:39.070 --> 00:11:42.350
- I haven't sold anything!
-What's the difference?


82
00:12:02.870 --> 00:12:05.750
The city?
The city's a frightening force.


83
00:12:05.950 --> 00:12:08.150
And the biggerthe city,
the stronger it is.


84
00:12:08.350 --> 00:12:12.750
It sucks you in.
Only the strong can climb out.


85
00:12:14.670 --> 00:12:16.270
And even so...

86
00:12:23.270 --> 00:12:26.550
-What's your name?
- Hoffman.


87
00:12:26.870 --> 00:12:30.150
-What are you, a Jew?
- I'm German.


88
00:12:30.350 --> 00:12:33.350
Oh... I'm not wild about Jews...

89
00:12:33.670 --> 00:12:36.550
-And Germans?
- Germans? They're okay.


90
00:12:36.870 --> 00:12:39.750
-What's the difference?
-Why you badgering me about it?


91
00:12:45.070 --> 00:12:48.550
-Where have you taken me?
- My homeland.


92
00:12:50.150 --> 00:12:52.270
My ancestors lie here.

93
00:12:57.870 --> 00:12:59.550
Sit down.

94
00:13:04.470 --> 00:13:07.350
- Here.
- Hold on.


95
00:13:07.950 --> 00:13:09.950
What?

96
00:13:10.150 --> 00:13:14.350
I brought a present for my brother.
I guess it wasn't to be.


97
00:13:23.550 --> 00:13:25.470
Oh, gimme some of that...

98
00:13:37.950 --> 00:13:40.350
She's a doll.

99
00:13:40.870 --> 00:13:43.470
Hey, girl, what's your name?

100
00:13:47.870 --> 00:13:49.470
Tickets, please.

101
00:13:50.670 --> 00:13:52.550
No ticket.

102
00:13:52.870 --> 00:13:54.750
Tickets, please.

103
00:13:58.270 --> 00:14:00.150
No ticket.

104
00:14:00.950 --> 00:14:02.750
Your tickets, please.

105
00:14:03.070 --> 00:14:05.750
Listen, you Russian or what?

106
00:14:05.950 --> 00:14:08.470
I'm saying to you in Russian:
no ticket.


107
00:14:08.670 --> 00:14:10.750
Then pay the fine, please.

108
00:14:10.950 --> 00:14:13.750
What fine, huh?
I'm an invalid.


109
00:14:15.270 --> 00:14:17.750
You pay the fine or show me
your ticket.


110
00:14:17.950 --> 00:14:22.550
Hey, take a load off your feet.
Sit down.


111
00:14:22.870 --> 00:14:25.750
Well, if you haven't got tickets,
then you have to pay the fine.


112
00:14:28.870 --> 00:14:31.550
Hey, don't you understand?

113
00:14:34.870 --> 00:14:36.350
Come on, come on.

114
00:14:36.950 --> 00:14:38.950
Pay the fine!

115
00:14:42.150 --> 00:14:43.950
Brother, don't kill me!

116
00:14:44.270 --> 00:14:47.150
The money,
take it all, take it!


117
00:14:47.350 --> 00:14:49.350
Don't kill me, brother!

118
00:14:51.470 --> 00:14:54.550
You're not my brother,
you blackassed worm!


119
00:14:57.350 --> 00:14:59.870
- How much is the fine?
- Seven.


120
00:15:03.470 --> 00:15:04.950
Run!

121
00:15:39.270 --> 00:15:44.350
Hey, guys!
It's not ''Nora'', it's ''Norah''.


122
00:15:48.950 --> 00:15:51.550
In short, you know, to get there
you've got to...


123
00:16:03.870 --> 00:16:05.270
Bye!

124
00:16:07.350 --> 00:16:10.750
Man, oh man, that's such a cool
Walkman! Let me listen.


125
00:16:18.150 --> 00:16:21.750
Why you blasting this crap?
Have you got anything decent?


126
00:16:21.950 --> 00:16:24.750
-Are you deaf or something?
- No.


127
00:16:24.950 --> 00:16:28.550
Your Walkman's fine,
but you're dressed like a pig.


128
00:16:28.950 --> 00:16:32.070
You got any acid?
Or dough?


129
00:16:32.270 --> 00:16:34.750
Got any dough?
- No.


130
00:16:35.070 --> 00:16:38.070
I'm Kat.
You can always find me here.


131
00:16:38.270 --> 00:16:42.150
If you get some money, come here
and we'll get stoned. Well, later!


132
00:16:55.270 --> 00:16:57.150
It's open!

133
00:17:12.670 --> 00:17:15.070
On your knees! Hands out!

134
00:17:15.270 --> 00:17:18.270
I'm looking for my brother.
Viktor Bagrov. He lived here.


135
00:17:19.070 --> 00:17:22.270
I'm his younger brother.
Been in Leningrad two days.


136
00:17:22.470 --> 00:17:26.350
My mom gave me his address:
Moika 1, apartment 8.


137
00:17:28.670 --> 00:17:31.750
Well, hello, brother!

138
00:17:36.950 --> 00:17:39.350
It's not Leningrad,
but St. Petersburg.


139
00:17:40.270 --> 00:17:43.870
St. Pete's, for short.
A beautiful city, but a province.


140
00:17:44.870 --> 00:17:48.550
Got to go to Moscow.
All the power's there.


141
00:17:48.870 --> 00:17:51.750
I'll scrape it a little more here,
and then to Moscow.


142
00:17:52.270 --> 00:17:55.150
- How's mom?
- Okay.


143
00:17:59.550 --> 00:18:01.750
Here, she sent you this.

144
00:18:03.070 --> 00:18:07.350
Come on, drink. I still got
some business to take care of.


145
00:18:18.870 --> 00:18:20.750
This'll hold you over for awhile.

146
00:18:24.070 --> 00:18:28.270
Get some nice clothes,
rent an apartment or a room.


147
00:18:30.350 --> 00:18:33.950
Nothing over a hundred for now
and then we'll see.


148
00:18:37.950 --> 00:18:41.750
- How was the army?
- Okay.


149
00:18:43.270 --> 00:18:45.750
Mom wrote that you were in the war.

150
00:18:46.670 --> 00:18:50.750
Nah. I sat things out at HQ.
I was a clerk.


151
00:18:54.150 --> 00:18:56.350
Can you shoot?

152
00:18:56.670 --> 00:18:58.950
Yeah, they took us out
to the shooting range.


153
00:19:08.670 --> 00:19:11.070
Hello.
Do you have ''Wings'' by Nautilus?


154
00:19:13.070 --> 00:19:14.750
Well, just give me what you got.

155
00:20:44.950 --> 00:20:47.750
He's an ex
-Chechen terrorist.

156
00:20:47.950 --> 00:20:50.750
They've moved into St. Pete
from Moscow too.


157
00:20:50.950 --> 00:20:53.150
Grabbing up everything, brother.

158
00:20:53.870 --> 00:20:55.350
I already told you about it.

159
00:20:56.670 --> 00:20:59.750
Took this market.
Now he's squeezing Russians out.


160
00:20:59.950 --> 00:21:02.350
And I got a
piece of the action there.

161
00:21:02.550 --> 00:21:07.270
So he came down hard. He knows we're
weak now, so he's strangling us.


162
00:21:07.470 --> 00:21:11.950
He bought off everyone there.
And killed the ones he didn't buy up.


163
00:21:12.150 --> 00:21:17.750
And so it's my turn, Danny.
If I don't pay...


164
00:21:22.870 --> 00:21:26.750
So it's either him or us.
That's how it is, brother.


165
00:21:31.470 --> 00:21:33.550
He loves walking around the market
during the day.


166
00:21:33.870 --> 00:21:36.750
Inspects his holdings, the creep.

167
00:21:36.950 --> 00:21:38.950
This is the best place.

168
00:21:39.150 --> 00:21:42.550
His bodyguards are always with him:
two or three guerillas.


169
00:21:42.870 --> 00:21:45.950
All darkies. With rods. Beasts.

170
00:21:47.350 --> 00:21:49.550
All in all, the job's not easy.

171
00:21:49.870 --> 00:21:53.150
You size things up and think
how you'll make your exit.


172
00:21:54.150 --> 00:21:57.470
I'd better give the money to you.
Two thousand bucks.


173
00:21:57.670 --> 00:21:59.950
Don't come to my place anymore,
it's dangerous.


174
00:22:00.550 --> 00:22:02.750
If something comes up, give me a ring.

175
00:22:04.270 --> 00:22:07.470
Here's a barrel and a clip.
That's another six hundred.


176
00:22:07.670 --> 00:22:10.750
-We'll settle up later.
- I'll get by.


177
00:22:38.470 --> 00:22:42.350
Hello. It's us.
The Tatar wasn't there.


178
00:22:49.270 --> 00:22:52.350
- How much for potatoes?
- One and a half.


179
00:24:25.670 --> 00:24:27.550
How's business?

180
00:24:29.270 --> 00:24:31.150
Ah, who cares?

181
00:24:31.870 --> 00:24:36.070
Only that thug and his pals are here,
looking for you.


182
00:24:36.950 --> 00:24:39.150
Listen, German. 
I need a room.

183
00:24:39.350 --> 00:24:42.350
A small one. Downtown.
In a quiet neighborhood.


184
00:24:42.550 --> 00:24:44.470
Ask your people, okay?

185
00:24:46.070 --> 00:24:47.270
Here.

186
00:24:52.870 --> 00:24:54.350
Thanks.

187
00:24:56.270 --> 00:25:01.350
- Did you find your brother?
- I found him.


188
00:25:20.670 --> 00:25:23.550
-Who is it?
- It's me, Zinka. Open up.


189
00:25:23.950 --> 00:25:29.550
Zinka? Who the heck's Zinka?
Get outta here, whore.


190
00:25:29.870 --> 00:25:34.070
Have you lost your fucking mind, old
man? Open up! It's me, Zinka!


191
00:25:34.270 --> 00:25:37.350
What a fool! His brain's rotted!

192
00:25:38.870 --> 00:25:41.750
-What do you want?
- I brought you a lodger.


193
00:25:45.670 --> 00:25:47.350
Get it out!

194
00:25:51.550 --> 00:25:53.470
People walking around...

195
00:26:05.470 --> 00:26:08.350
So, old man, you got all mangy here
without me?


196
00:28:34.870 --> 00:28:36.750
Hey, you, kind sir!

197
00:28:37.870 --> 00:28:39.470
Buy a watermelon.

198
00:28:41.750 --> 00:28:44.750
- Is it good?
- Sure! Look what a beauty!


199
00:28:45.470 --> 00:28:49.350
-Yesterday I ate 7 of them myself.
- Okay.


200
00:28:49.870 --> 00:28:52.750
- How much?
- Only six thousand.


201
00:28:54.670 --> 00:28:57.070
Thanks. Enjoy it!

202
00:29:41.950 --> 00:29:44.470
Lord! What's going on?

203
00:29:44.670 --> 00:29:46.670
There, the guy with the watermelon!

204
00:31:58.870 --> 00:32:00.350
Maybe you need help, huh?

205
00:32:01.270 --> 00:32:04.150
I'm outta here. Keep driving.
I'll find you.


206
00:32:40.670 --> 00:32:43.550
It wasn't the Tatar. A young guy.

207
00:32:44.150 --> 00:32:47.070
He did everything first class.
A real pro.


208
00:32:47.270 --> 00:32:50.270
The Chechen kicked the bucket,
and that guy just walked off.


209
00:32:50.470 --> 00:32:53.750
He hopped in a yellow tram
and was off.


210
00:32:53.950 --> 00:32:55.950
I winged him, the motherfucker.

211
00:32:56.150 --> 00:32:58.350
But the bitch greased Pinecone.

212
00:32:58.670 --> 00:33:00.550
Pinecone? Whacked him dead?

213
00:33:00.870 --> 00:33:03.470
Don't know. They took him
to the hospital.


214
00:33:03.670 --> 00:33:06.350
Why were you shooting
if it wasn't the Tatar?


215
00:33:06.670 --> 00:33:08.350
Well, you know, I...

216
00:33:08.670 --> 00:33:11.550
It's the Tatar we have to pay.

217
00:33:11.870 --> 00:33:13.750
You shit-for-brains!

218
00:33:21.350 --> 00:33:24.350
But that the new guy whacked
Pinecone is fine.


219
00:33:24.550 --> 00:33:26.270
They won't suspect us.

220
00:33:28.070 --> 00:33:29.750
Well, Tatar!..

221
00:33:30.950 --> 00:33:34.350
His life hangs by a thread,
but he thinks about the bread.


222
00:33:43.270 --> 00:33:45.150
We should take you to the hospital.

223
00:33:45.950 --> 00:33:48.350
I can't go to the hospital, German.

224
00:33:52.470 --> 00:33:57.750
It's okay, German...
We'll get through.


225
00:34:11.950 --> 00:34:15.150
Zinka! Zinka!

226
00:34:17.150 --> 00:34:21.150
If I'd met you outside Kursk
in '43...


227
00:34:21.350 --> 00:34:24.550
- Beat it, old fool. What do you want?
- Come here.


228
00:34:27.270 --> 00:34:30.950
Get some more vodka, strong stuff,

229
00:34:31.950 --> 00:34:36.270
and bandages at the drugstore,
and... streptomycin.


230
00:34:36.870 --> 00:34:39.550
And antibiotics.

231
00:34:49.070 --> 00:34:53.550
And get something for Gramps,
so he stops pestering us.


232
00:34:53.870 --> 00:34:55.350
Okay.

233
00:35:04.870 --> 00:35:06.750
You're a smart man, German.

234
00:35:09.870 --> 00:35:12.750
Tell me: what do we live for?

235
00:35:13.670 --> 00:35:15.950
Well, everyone decides himself.

236
00:35:16.870 --> 00:35:19.750
There's this saying:

237
00:35:20.870 --> 00:35:23.750
''What's good forthe Russian
is death for the German.''


238
00:35:24.950 --> 00:35:27.150
I live to disprove this.

239
00:35:32.350 --> 00:35:34.350
Do you have a gal?

240
00:35:38.470 --> 00:35:40.350
What about Zinka?

241
00:35:42.350 --> 00:35:45.350
It's probably 'cause of her
you took a shot in the eye?


242
00:35:52.870 --> 00:35:54.350
Never mind.

243
00:35:58.270 --> 00:36:00.550
You're a good man, German.

244
