is not Russian way.


496
01:12:29.950 --> 01:12:33.550
I asked you not to deceive your
husband. It's not Christian.


497
01:12:33.870 --> 01:12:38.350
I really don't know where he lives
and what he's doing.


498
01:12:39.270 --> 01:12:40.750
Everything's clean.

499
01:12:41.350 --> 01:12:45.350
He was here for two days.
He found me himself.


500
01:12:45.550 --> 01:12:49.750
I kicked him out.
I'm telling you the truth.


501
01:12:54.670 --> 01:12:57.950
If you like your honey sweet,
you should like the bees indeed.


502
01:13:01.070 --> 01:13:07.550
Let me go, creeps!
Don't touch me, scum!


503
01:13:07.870 --> 01:13:09.550
Let me go!

504
01:13:10.350 --> 01:13:12.750
Ouch! I'll kill you, bitch!

505
01:13:12.950 --> 01:13:15.950
- Scum!
- Lie down!


506
01:14:42.870 --> 01:14:44.470
I'll kill the motherfucker!

507
01:14:50.870 --> 01:14:56.750
Your people stopped by.
They asked for you.


508
01:14:59.870 --> 01:15:02.750
I really don't know
who you are and where you live.


509
01:15:04.670 --> 01:15:06.550
They didn't believe me.

510
01:15:19.870 --> 01:15:23.350
Their chief had a round mug,

511
01:15:24.670 --> 01:15:26.750
talked in proverbs.

512
01:15:29.350 --> 01:15:30.950
Shall we sing a song?

513
01:15:34.270 --> 01:15:36.150
I'm tone deaf.

514
01:15:38.270 --> 01:15:40.350
Yeah, I understand.

515
01:15:44.870 --> 01:15:48.470
You say he served at HQ?
As a clerk?


516
01:15:50.150 --> 01:15:54.070
First Pinecone, then two more
disappeared.


517
01:15:55.670 --> 01:15:59.150
And now the Mole.
Simple like that.


518
01:16:10.270 --> 01:16:13.750
You live, you learn,
you live and learn.


519
01:16:15.950 --> 01:16:21.950
Yeah. Danny, is that you?
What happened?


520
01:16:23.470 --> 01:16:26.750
Something happened, brother.
You alone?


521
01:16:29.270 --> 01:16:31.550
Good. I'll be there soon
and tell you everything.


522
01:16:43.270 --> 01:16:44.750
He's coming.

523
01:16:59.950 --> 01:17:02.950
-What do you want?
- Gramps, sell me your rifle.


524
01:17:03.550 --> 01:17:06.150
-A million.
- Bring it out.


525
01:17:06.670 --> 01:17:08.750
Give me the money first.

526
01:17:14.270 --> 01:17:17.150
- Dollars!
- There's a million two hundred here.


527
01:17:17.350 --> 01:17:19.750
Drag out all the shells.

528
01:17:34.670 --> 01:17:36.950
Five caliber. For ducks.

529
01:20:41.350 --> 01:20:43.750
You lie here quiet, 
I'll let you go.

530
01:21:03.470 --> 01:21:05.270
All right. I got it.

531
01:21:09.150 --> 01:21:13.350
Guns on the floor! Hands behind your
heads! Lie down, mugs on the floor!


532
01:21:47.950 --> 01:21:49.350
Viktor, get up.

533
01:21:49.670 --> 01:21:52.750
Don't shoot, brother. Please.

534
01:21:52.950 --> 01:21:55.350
What you saying, brother? Come on,
get up, it's over.


535
01:21:55.870 --> 01:22:00.750
Forgive me, brother.
Don't shoot, please. Don't kill me.


536
01:22:00.950 --> 01:22:05.750
Brother. You're my brother.
You were like a father to me.


537
01:22:07.870 --> 01:22:11.550
I even called you papa.

538
01:22:13.870 --> 01:22:16.150
You remember how I cut my leg
when we went fishing?


539
01:22:16.350 --> 01:22:18.750
You dragged me home,
ten kilometers.


540
01:22:21.270 --> 01:22:26.350
Remember how I got scared of a cat-
fish? And you just laughed at me?


541
01:22:31.550 --> 01:22:32.870
You promised.

542
01:22:35.070 --> 01:22:37.550
I keep my word.

543
01:22:39.550 --> 01:22:42.750
And you tell your people: I'll whack
whoever touches my brother.


544
01:22:43.870 --> 01:22:45.150
Go.

545
01:22:46.350 --> 01:22:50.750
- It was him who betrayed you.
- I know.


546
01:22:50.950 --> 01:22:53.750
- Forgive me, brother.
- Cut it out.


547
01:22:54.870 --> 01:22:56.750
Where's the money?

548
01:22:58.550 --> 01:23:02.270
In his briefcase.
He took everything, the creep.


549
01:23:15.270 --> 01:23:17.750
You go home. To mama.

550
01:23:19.070 --> 01:23:23.350
She's getting old.
Needs help.


551
01:23:26.550 --> 01:23:28.470
Give her the money.

552
01:23:31.150 --> 01:23:35.070
Get a job, with the police.

553
01:23:36.550 --> 01:23:39.750
Uncle Kolya is the chief there,

554
01:23:39.950 --> 01:23:42.150
he was dad's classmate.

555
01:23:46.550 --> 01:23:48.470
They've got an opening.

556
01:23:52.070 --> 01:23:53.950
Don't take the train.

557
01:23:55.870 --> 01:23:58.350
Hitchhike out of the city.

558
01:24:10.350 --> 01:24:14.350
Well, brother? So long.

559
01:24:18.870 --> 01:24:20.550
If God wills it, we'll see each other
sometime.


560
01:24:23.470 --> 01:24:25.750
Did you forget, you piece of shit?

561
01:24:26.070 --> 01:24:28.950
You forgot what I told you?

562
01:24:29.870 --> 01:24:33.550
-You forgot?
- Pavel!


563
01:24:33.870 --> 01:24:35.750
I'll break you of your whoring!

564
01:24:41.670 --> 01:24:44.470
I'll make that fancy pants little
retard of yours eat shit!


565
01:24:45.350 --> 01:24:48.350
Where is he?
Where's that asshole? Huh?


566
01:24:48.550 --> 01:24:49.950
Here I am.

567
01:24:51.470 --> 01:24:54.350
Ah! Mr. Cool's arrived.

568
01:24:55.870 --> 01:24:58.350
Well, brother, how we gonna
split the bitch?


569
01:24:58.870 --> 01:25:00.750
You're not my brother.

570
01:25:03.870 --> 01:25:05.350
Pavel!

571
01:25:07.870 --> 01:25:11.070
Take your hands of it!
Hold on, hold on.


572
01:25:12.270 --> 01:25:13.750
It's okay, Pavel, it's okay.

573
01:25:13.950 --> 01:25:17.150
Quiet, quiet.
It's okay, Pavel.


574
01:25:26.350 --> 01:25:27.350
Sveta!

575
01:25:27.950 --> 01:25:31.150
Come on, shoot!
Kill everybody, come on!


576
01:25:31.950 --> 01:25:33.950
You're the big man here!

577
01:25:34.150 --> 01:25:37.070
What's it cost you to kill a man?
You, a clerk!


578
01:25:38.270 --> 01:25:40.270
- Sveta!
- Get out!


579
01:25:40.470 --> 01:25:42.150
Get me a towel.

580
01:25:43.270 --> 01:25:45.750
Sveta, I came foryou.

581
01:25:47.870 --> 01:25:51.350
I got money. Can we leave?

582
01:25:51.670 --> 01:25:55.070
Quiet, Pavel, quiet.
We'll take care of you.


583
01:25:56.870 --> 01:25:59.750
- Sveta!
- I told you to leave.


584
01:26:00.670 --> 01:26:02.750
Don't come here anymore.

585
01:26:03.670 --> 01:26:05.550
I don't love you.

586
01:26:06.670 --> 01:26:09.950
It's okay, Pavel.
Everything's going to be fine.


587
01:26:19.670 --> 01:26:22.070
I brought you an album.

588
01:26:33.350 --> 01:26:39.550
This money... since you got it...
give some... for treatment.


589
01:26:40.350 --> 01:26:42.470
You see how it is...

590
01:28:03.870 --> 01:28:08.350
You said it: the city is a force.
And here everyone's weak.


591
01:28:11.870 --> 01:28:16.750
The city is a dark force. The strong
come here and become weak.


592
01:28:17.870 --> 01:28:19.750
The city takes our strength.

593
01:28:22.950 --> 01:28:24.950
And now you've fallen.

594
01:28:30.950 --> 01:28:32.750
Here, take this.

595
01:28:35.670 --> 01:28:39.350
What's the problem? Take it. There's
a lot here. You'll live for a while.


596
01:28:43.670 --> 01:28:46.550
What's good for the Russian
is death forthe German.


597
01:29:11.470 --> 01:29:14.550
Okay, German, so long.

598
01:29:18.470 --> 01:29:19.950
Thank you.

599
01:29:51.870 --> 01:29:53.750
Guys, have you seen Kat?

600
01:29:53.950 --> 01:29:56.350
Look in McDonalds.

601
01:30:19.870 --> 01:30:23.950
If it's because of the dough, you're
wasting your time. I didn't take it.


602
01:30:26.270 --> 01:30:30.150
-What are you going to do?
- I don't know.


603
01:30:30.870 --> 01:30:34.670
I may go to the Pyramid, or to the
Planetarium, only it's expensive.


604
01:30:35.870 --> 01:30:37.750
Penkin's playing today.

605
01:30:38.470 --> 01:30:40.350
Right now it's too early to think.

606
01:30:43.350 --> 01:30:46.550
Pinocchio, dish out sixty thousand.

607
01:30:46.870 --> 01:30:49.750
We'll each take a hit of acid.
And in the evening I'll treat you.


608
01:30:52.470 --> 01:30:54.150
I'm leaving town.

609
01:30:57.550 --> 01:30:59.470
What did you want then?

610
01:31:01.270 --> 01:31:04.350
- To say goodbye.
-Well, later.


611
01:31:12.870 --> 01:31:15.350
Take it. Go see the Penkin concert.

612
01:31:19.670 --> 01:31:21.150
What's this for?

613
01:31:24.550 --> 01:31:26.470
Is this for me or something?

614
01:31:26.670 --> 01:31:28.670
Okay, later.

615
01:31:30.470 --> 01:31:32.350
Maybe you need something?

616
01:31:34.270 --> 01:31:35.750
Well, I'm outta here?

617
01:32:10.150 --> 01:32:12.070
I haven't sat out my discharge yet.

618
01:32:13.670 --> 01:32:15.550
Where did you serve?

619
01:32:16.670 --> 01:32:20.350
In HQ there, I sat out my hitch
as a clerk, you know...


620
01:32:21.670 --> 01:32:23.550
And what do you want to be?

621
01:32:23.870 --> 01:32:27.750
Me? Don't know.
A driver.


622
01:32:34.070 --> 01:32:36.070
Hey, can I switch on some music?

623
01:32:36.270 --> 01:32:38.270
I haven't listened to it for awhile.

624
01:32:38.470 --> 01:32:39.870
Go ahead.

625
01:33:01.070 --> 01:33:02.950
The snow's really piled up, huh?

626
01:33:07.150 --> 01:33:08.750
Yeah.

627
01:33:13.070 --> 01:33:14.950
Where you headed?

628
01:33:17.470 --> 01:33:19.350
To Moscow.